articles.description: MaCio Teague scored 14 points, including UNC Asheville's last nine points, and his step-back 3-pointer from the wing with 4.4 seconds left gave the Bulldogs a 66-64 win over Radford on Saturday.
articles.headline: Teague's late 3s send UNC Asheville past Radford 66-64

articles.description: Quentin Goodin made two free throws with three-tenths of a second left, allowing fifth-ranked Xavier to hold off Creighton 72-71 on Saturday.
articles.headline: Goodin's last-second FTs push No. 5 Xavier past Creighton

images.caption: Creighton's Toby Hegmen fouls Quentin Goodin as he charges the lane. Goodin makes both free throws to seal a win for the Musketeers.
images.name: Costly foul gives Xavier win in final seconds

articles.description: Big men will be the focal points in a nationally televised Big Ten Conference game on Sunday as Wisconsin redshirt junior forward Ethan Happ and Michigan junior forward Moritz Wagner take their talents to the Kohl Center court in Madison, Wis.
articles.headline: Battle of big men highlight Michigan-Wisconsin clash

articles.description: Kahron Ross scored 30 points and Lehigh won its fourth straight, its second straight in overtime, when the Mountain Hawks held off American, 80-78 in a Patriot League battle on Saturday afternoon.
articles.headline: Ross' 30 pts lead red-hot Lehigh past American in OT, 80-78

articles.description: Trae Young's 22 points and 11 points is not enough to prevent No. 17 Oklahoma from being upset by Iowa State 88-80.
articles.headline: Young, Oklahoma drop third straight

images.caption: Trae Young's 22 points and 11 points is not enough to prevent No. 17 Oklahoma from being upset by Iowa State 88-80.
images.name: Young, Oklahoma drop third straight

articles.description: Vasa Pusica scored 23 points with four rebounds and four assists and Northeastern notched its third-straight win, beating Towson 77-62 on Saturday.
articles.headline: Pusica with 23 points, Northeastern beats Towson 77-62
